In this White House press briefing, Press Secretary Robert Gibbs makes several announcements. President Obama will be visiting Riyadh, Saudi Arabia to meet with King Abdullah and discuss important issues such as Middle East peace, Iran, and terrorism. The President also released the 60-day Cyberspace Policy Review Report, highlighting the importance of cybersecurity. Gibbs discusses the confirmation process for Judge Sotomayor, the President's Supreme Court nominee, and addresses criticisms of her record. He also mentions the ongoing situation with North Korea and the engagement of China. Finally, Gibbs responds to questions about the Governor of Nevada declining to meet with the President and the California Supreme Court decision on Prop 8.